WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:04.000 --> 00:06.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:08.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:17.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:17.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ He's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:27.000
[ Birds chirping ]

00:27.000 --> 00:30.000
♪♪

00:30.000 --> 00:31.000
[ Seat belts click ]

00:31.000 --> 00:34.000
Okay, JP. You ready, buddy?

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
Uh, I -- I think so.

00:36.000 --> 00:37.000
C'mon, JP!

00:37.000 --> 00:38.000
The entire fate of our summer

00:38.000 --> 00:39.000
is depending on you!

00:39.000 --> 00:40.000
He knows that!

00:40.000 --> 00:41.000
We're all very clear on

00:41.000 --> 00:44.000
what's going on in this situation, okay?

00:44.000 --> 00:47.000
Racers! On ya marks.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
-Vroom vroom! -Get set!

00:49.000 --> 00:52.000
[ Twinkle! ]

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
Race!

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
It's the First Annual Creek Kart Race!

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
A free-for-all downhill derby where anything goes!

00:59.000 --> 01:04.000
The grand prize: exclusive access to the new in-ground pool

01:05.000 --> 01:06.000
in my parents' backyard!

01:06.000 --> 01:11.000
Enter now and you'll be drowning in fun -- uhh, while you swim!

01:11.000 --> 01:12.000
Whoa! Wow!

01:13.000 --> 01:16.000
Pool pass! A pool pass.

01:16.000 --> 01:18.000
Kelsey was enticed by the chance

01:18.000 --> 01:19.000
to soothe her war-weary muscles

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
in the chlorinated oasis.

01:21.000 --> 01:22.000
The only armor she'd don --

01:22.000 --> 01:25.000
sunscreen... and perhaps a pool floatie

01:25.000 --> 01:28.000
given to her by the selkie artisans at swim lessons.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
Oh, man, I love races!

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
The crashes, the adrenaline, the corporate sponsorship.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.000
Everyone, everyone make way! [ Rings bell ]

01:36.000 --> 01:38.000
[ Thud ] Make way, I say!

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
Miss Eliza of the Tea Timers is making an entrance!

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
My, my, Miss Jane. It sounds like the common-folk

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
are holding a little competition.

01:47.000 --> 01:49.000
How precious.

01:49.000 --> 01:50.000
It's amusing what the little people do

01:50.000 --> 01:53.000
to entertain their sad lives.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
[ Giggling ] Indeed.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.000
But if you ask me,

01:57.000 --> 01:59.000
this whole thing sounds a bit barbaric

01:59.000 --> 02:00.000
for our precious little creek.

02:00.000 --> 02:04.000
I guess it's up to us to bring this race some poise and grace.

02:04.000 --> 02:08.000
I'll have daddy buy me a car, and we'll surely win this race!

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
[ Speaking with lisp ] Not a chance!

02:10.000 --> 02:13.000
Because us Forest Scouts are the heroes of this story.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.000
And we're going to win with our secret weapon!

02:15.000 --> 02:19.000
A silly racing badge you will just repeatedly point to?

02:19.000 --> 02:23.000
Uh, no! We'll be entering a mystery driver!

02:23.000 --> 02:28.000
Racer J! He's a foreign exchange scout from another country.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
Yeah. [ Laughs ]

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
He's cool and daring and handsome,

02:32.000 --> 02:33.000
and everyone's gonna love him.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Yo, is there a race going on? I'd be down to join.

02:37.000 --> 02:38.000
Ooh! Yeah! All right!

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
It's Cannonball from the 10 Speeds!

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
He's never lost a race in his life!

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
He's the fastest kid in the creek!

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
I roll pretty fast, that doesn't mean I'm better

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
or worse than anyone else. [ Scoffs ]

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
None of these chumps are worthy of the glory

02:51.000 --> 02:52.000
of an in-ground pool. Yeah.

02:52.000 --> 02:55.000
One of us should definitely enter. Just imagine it.

02:55.000 --> 02:58.000
Roaring through the creek at a million miles a minute.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
Your orange Jersey whipping in the wind.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
Your best friends, Craig and Kelsey,

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
cheering you on from the side lines

03:04.000 --> 03:05.000
as you approach the finish! [ Gasps ]

03:05.000 --> 03:07.000
I'll do it! Oh, yeah, yeah.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
You should -- you should totally enter the race, Craig.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
You'd build the best cart in the whole creek.

03:13.000 --> 03:20.000
♪♪

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
I'll see you all at the finish line.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
Right after you eat my dust!

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
If I'm gonna build this kart,

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
then we're gonna need some parts.

03:28.000 --> 03:29.000
Are you sure that junklord's gonna let you

03:29.000 --> 03:30.000
take the stuff you need?

03:30.000 --> 03:33.000
He's pretty clingy. Aw, come on.

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
Building a race car is the coolest thing ever.

03:35.000 --> 03:37.000
Who would say no to that?

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
No! What do you mean "no"?

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
I thought you changed?! I have changed!

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
I gave away stuff the last time you were here,

03:44.000 --> 03:47.000
and I'll get rid of more junk, uhh, next year.

03:47.000 --> 03:49.000
[ Whispers ] Craig, corporate sponsorship.

03:49.000 --> 03:53.000
Well, how about you sponsor us? The junk will still be yours,

03:53.000 --> 03:55.000
you'd just be letting us borrow it.

03:55.000 --> 03:57.000
We'll paint your name on the side,

03:57.000 --> 03:59.000
and it'll be real cool.

03:59.000 --> 04:02.000
Hmm. I've always wanted to be a brand name.

04:02.000 --> 04:06.000
Junk Lorde with an "e". Very well.

04:06.000 --> 04:09.000
I guess I can sponsor your cause.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.000
In ya go!

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
Got that trash can you asked for!

04:12.000 --> 04:13.000
Aw, that's perfect for the body!

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
Okay, now we just need four wheels.

04:15.000 --> 04:18.000
Wheels? What do you need wheels for!?

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
This rolls just fine by itself!

04:20.000 --> 04:22.000
Ugh, fine!

04:22.000 --> 04:25.000
You just take and take and take!

04:25.000 --> 04:27.000
Oh, man, dance mat!

04:27.000 --> 04:30.000
The perfect stage for some freestyle vogue.

04:30.000 --> 04:37.000
[ Disco music plays ] Mm, da, da, mm, ahh, laa, yeah.

04:37.000 --> 04:40.000
Ooh.

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
Hmm? Whoa!

04:42.000 --> 04:46.000
[ Gasps ] Ohh!

04:46.000 --> 04:49.000
Oh, man. Smooth moves, JP!

04:50.000 --> 04:52.000
[ Laughs ] Thank you!

04:53.000 --> 04:54.000
All right, just one last tire.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
Can someone please pass me the wrench?

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
Mortimer's got it.

04:58.000 --> 05:05.000
♪♪

05:05.000 --> 05:09.000
Thank you, Mortimer. [ Grunting ]

05:09.000 --> 05:12.000
That ought to do it. Check it out.

05:12.000 --> 05:13.000
This beast has got an all-terrain,

05:13.000 --> 05:15.000
bi-shovel rock plow on the front,

05:15.000 --> 05:18.000
an extra propulsional box fan in the back.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.000
Wheels.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
And all kinds of secret gadgets!

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
Cool!

05:23.000 --> 05:24.000
[ Seat belt clicks ]

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
You ready to test this bad boy out?

05:26.000 --> 05:27.000
Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait, wait!

05:27.000 --> 05:29.000
I got your helmet ready for you.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.000
It's actually mine, but it'll look better on you.

05:31.000 --> 05:33.000
The flames will make it look like you're going faster,

05:33.000 --> 05:36.000
and the backwards "R" is charming because we're children.

05:36.000 --> 05:39.000
All right, let's see what this baby can do.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.000
Yeah! Go, Craig!

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Hah! It's working!

05:42.000 --> 05:45.000
I can actually drive! I'm driving! I'm --

05:45.000 --> 05:46.000
Ooh.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
[ Yells ]

05:49.000 --> 05:52.000
Craig! Craig!

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
Give it to me straight, Kelsey. How bad is it?

05:54.000 --> 05:57.000
It doesn't look good. You skinned your knee.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
We're talking a level 4 boo boo.

05:59.000 --> 06:03.000
Aw man, that's gonna leave a nasty scab.

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
Aw, but it's gonna peel like a dream.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.000
I guess that's it. I can't race.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
Our cart will have to wait till next year.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
Along with our dreams of using Sailor Boy's pool.

06:13.000 --> 06:15.000
-I could do it. -What?

06:16.000 --> 06:17.000
I could do it. I want to do it.

06:18.000 --> 06:19.000
Yeah, JP would be perfect!

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
Remember that stunt he pulled at the junk pile!

06:21.000 --> 06:23.000
He rode that piece of cardboard

06:23.000 --> 06:27.000
like it was a piece of magic cardboard!

06:27.000 --> 06:28.000
Yeah.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
So you use that stick to steer the cart.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
Okay, great!

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
And underneath there are the rest of the controls.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
Uhh.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.000
It's got accelerators, defense mechanisms,

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
spring systems. Do you want me to explain them

06:39.000 --> 06:41.000
in alphabetical order or numerical?

06:41.000 --> 06:44.000
Can I wing it? I'm usually my best just winging things.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
JP, those other racers are not gonna pull any punches.

06:48.000 --> 06:50.000
You're gonna need all the help you can get.

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
Okay. I got an idea.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.000
I'll put my phone here so I can coach you through the race!

06:54.000 --> 06:57.000
It'll be like I'm right there at the steering wheel with you!

06:57.000 --> 06:59.000
[ Sighs ] Well, you know best.

06:59.000 --> 07:03.000
♪♪

07:03.000 --> 07:06.000
Right this way, Miss Eliza.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.000
[ Tires squeal, mud splats ] Excuse me!

07:08.000 --> 07:12.000
Ugh, now I'm going to have to tell George to clean this up!

07:12.000 --> 07:13.000
George! Clean this up!

07:13.000 --> 07:15.000
Oh, sorry 'bout that.

07:15.000 --> 07:16.000
I'm just excited to win that pool pass.

07:17.000 --> 07:19.000
They don't call me Cannonball for nothing, you know.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.000
[ Panting ] Bon soir, everyone!

07:22.000 --> 07:25.000
It's me, the mysterious Racer J.

07:25.000 --> 07:27.000
Aren't I intriguingly handsome?

07:27.000 --> 07:28.000
Mm-hmm!

07:28.000 --> 07:30.000
C'mon, JP! The entire fate

07:30.000 --> 07:31.000
of our summer is depending on you!

07:31.000 --> 07:34.000
He knows that! We're all very clear

07:34.000 --> 07:36.000
on what's going on in this situation, okay?

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
[ Gulps, sighs ]

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
Racers! On ya marks.

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
-Vroom vroom. -Get set.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
[ Twinkle ]

07:46.000 --> 07:47.000
Race!

07:47.000 --> 07:51.000
[ Cheering ]

07:51.000 --> 07:52.000
Racer J was in the lead,

07:52.000 --> 07:54.000
but little did the other kids know,

07:54.000 --> 07:57.000
Racer J was actually Jason.

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
-Wassup, Jason? -H-Hey! I'm not Jason!

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
I'll see you at the finish line, Jason!

08:02.000 --> 08:03.000
Uhh, uhh.

08:03.000 --> 08:06.000
You're doing good, JP! But keep your eyes on the road!

08:06.000 --> 08:08.000
Wha!

08:08.000 --> 08:11.000
Miss Eliza, we appear to have a garbage heap

08:11.000 --> 08:13.000
barreling towards us.

08:13.000 --> 08:14.000
Hmm? I'll take care of it.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
My tea was getting cold, anyways.

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
♪♪

08:19.000 --> 08:22.000
JP! Quick! Activate the deflector shields!

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
-Uh -- -The red button!

08:24.000 --> 08:25.000
Oh!

08:25.000 --> 08:28.000
[ Splat! ]

08:28.000 --> 08:29.000
Yes! Woo!

08:29.000 --> 08:31.000
C'mon JP! I want that pool pass.

08:31.000 --> 08:34.000
Mama doesn't wanna share a birdbath with Mortimer anymore!

08:34.000 --> 08:37.000
Okay. If you do exactly as I say, we can pull this off!

08:37.000 --> 08:38.000
Now go left!

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
Uh, oh, okay! [ Tires squealing ]

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
Watch it, you crumb-bum.

08:42.000 --> 08:45.000
Great! Wait, what's that? A rock?!

08:45.000 --> 08:46.000
You're gonna have to use the rock plow!

08:46.000 --> 08:48.000
Uh -- can I just go around it?

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
Just crank the wheel!

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
-What wheel? -On your left!

08:52.000 --> 08:55.000
♪♪

08:55.000 --> 08:58.000
[ Coughing ] It all plowed in my mouth!

08:58.000 --> 08:59.000
[ Gasps ] He's slowing down.

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
You need a speed boost. You have to activate the fan!

09:02.000 --> 09:04.000
I don't know if that's a good idea!

09:04.000 --> 09:07.000
I can barely see! -C'mon, JP!

09:07.000 --> 09:08.000
This is it!

09:08.000 --> 09:09.000
[ Coughing ] Okay!

09:09.000 --> 09:11.000
I'm trying!

09:11.000 --> 09:14.000
[ Tires squealing ] Whoa! Ugh!

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
JP! JP! Are you okay?

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
Yeah, I think so. I'm sorry, guys.

09:19.000 --> 09:22.000
There's just so much going on with the directions

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
and the gizmos and the gadgets.

09:24.000 --> 09:26.000
Hey, it's okay. I'm gonna get you through this.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
Okay, first I want you -- Wait!

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Craig, don't say anything. Huh?

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
JP is a great driver because he follows his instincts.

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
But he can't do if we don't trust him.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.000
We gotta let him spread his wings and wing it!

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
[ Grunts ]

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
Okay, what do I do now?

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
-I can't tell you. -What?

09:44.000 --> 09:46.000
You trusted me to build the best cart in the creek.

09:47.000 --> 09:49.000
And I did. And it's so good.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
But now it's my turn to trust you.

09:51.000 --> 09:54.000
So just be JP and wing it!

09:55.000 --> 09:58.000
♪♪

09:58.000 --> 10:02.000
Racer J was going to win, and everyone would respect him.

10:02.000 --> 10:05.000
And then he would tell everyone to respect Jason.

10:05.000 --> 10:06.000
[ Rumble ] Huh?!

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
Mortimer says he's catching up! [ Gasps ] He is!

10:09.000 --> 10:12.000
But he still gotta pass Eliza and Cannonball.

10:12.000 --> 10:15.000
♪♪

10:15.000 --> 10:18.000
Whoo! Hoo-hoo-hoo!

10:19.000 --> 10:20.000
That's dope.

10:20.000 --> 10:22.000
Both: Whoa!

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
[ Grunts, thud ]

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
Oh-hoh-oh! You did it!

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
That was amazing!

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
Thanks for believing in me, guys.

10:30.000 --> 10:33.000
We may have lost, but we still looked the best.

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
George, please dispose of the car.

10:35.000 --> 10:38.000
I finally lost a race. The curse has been lifted.

10:39.000 --> 10:40.000
[ Grunts ]

10:40.000 --> 10:43.000
[ Gasps ] The "J" was for Jason?

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
Of course it was!

10:45.000 --> 10:46.000
Ladies and gentlemen!

10:46.000 --> 10:51.000
I now bestow the all-inclusive pool pass to --

10:51.000 --> 10:52.000
It's mine!

10:52.000 --> 10:54.000
I hope you're ready to swim with the Junk Lord!

10:54.000 --> 10:57.000
I just need to dig up some swim trunks from the clothes pile.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.000
Oh, dear.

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
Well, that pool's ruined.

11:03.000 --> 11:04.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ I know I don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:14.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow at the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:17.000
Just like I drew it.

11:17.000 --> 11:19.000
♪♪
